        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing N. D. Labadie.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Cant[onment] Jessup La.</placeName></p>

<p><date when="1830-12-20">December 20th. 1830</date></p>
<p>Dear sir.</p>

<p>It has been a long time since I had the pleasure of your 
acquaintance, but I beg leave to bring to your recollection The time you
passed<placeName> Fort Riply</placeName>, on the <placeName>Sabine </placeName>in <date n="xx-xx-1821">1821</date>.</p>

<p>The <persName>bearer </persName>of this <persName>Mr. N. D Labadie</persName> I beg leave to introduce to
your acquaintance, as, a, young Gentleman, who visits your <placeName>Country</placeName>
with a view of locating himself somewhere, in your <placeName>District of
Country</placeName>, Either in the profession of medicine or in the Mercantile
pursuits&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Mr. Labadie</persName> has been in the Employ of <persName>Harrison and Hopkins
</persName>for the last Eight Months and from what we have found, from That
Experience, we have no hesitation in introducing him to you as a
<persName>Gentleman </persName>worthy of the highest, respect, and one well qualified to
discharge the duties of his profession&#8212;</p>

<p>If you can render <persName>Mr. Labadie</persName> any services in the way of his 
making an advantageous location&#8212;you will not only place him under
particular obligations to you, but aliso your</p>

<p><persName>D R Hopkins  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

<p>[Addressed:] To <persName>Col. Stephen F, Austin</persName> <placeName>St. Phillipe de Austin
Texas </placeName>  Pr <persName>Mr Labadie</persName></p>



        </div1>
